	<h4>Spacing Classes</h4>
	<p>The Terra spacing scale is a set of predefined values that can be utilized across interfaces and components to keep spacing consistent between and within components.</p>
	<p>
		For spacing on all sides, the class follows this pattern: <code>.{property}-{size}</code><br />
		With a direction, the classes follow this pattern: <code>.{property}-{direction}-{size}</code><br />
		Responsive spacing classes follow this pattern: <code>.{property}-{direction}-{breakpoint}-{size}</code>
	</p>
	<p>Where <code>{property}</code> is one of the following:</p>
	<ul class="list-condensed">
		<li><code>pad</code> for padding</li>
		<li><code>margin</code> for margin</li>
	</ul>
	<p>Where <code>{breakpoint}</code> is one of the following:</p>
	<ul class="list-condensed">
		<li><code>sm</code> for small screen sizes and up</li>
		<li><code>md</code> for medium screen sizes and up</li>
		<li><code>lg</code> for large screen sizes and up</li>
	</ul>
	<p>Where <code>{direction}</code> is one of the following:</p>
	<ul class="list-condensed">
		<li><code>t</code> for top</li>
		<li><code>r</code> for right</li>
		<li><code>b</code> for bottom</li>
		<li><code>l</code> for left</li>
		<li><code>h</code> for horizontal, or left and right</li>
		<li><code>v</code> for vertical, or top and bottom</li>
	</ul>
	<p>Where <code>{size}</code> is one of the following:</p>
	<ul class="list-condensed">
		<li><code>none</code> for 0px</li>
		<li><code>micro</code> for 4px</li>
		<li><code>mini</code> for 8px</li>
		<li><code>xxs</code> for 12px</li>
		<li><code>xs</code> for 16px</li>
		<li><code>sm</code> for 24px</li>
		<li><code>md</code> for 32px</li>
		<li><code>lg</code> for 48px</li>
		<li><code>xl</code> for 64px</li>
		<li><code>xxl</code> for 72px</li>
		<li><code>super</code> for 96px</li>
		<li><code>mega</code> for 144px</li>
	</ul>
</div>
